4.25/5  rDev -6.8%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 3.25 |  overall: 4.25Thanks, Xenoreactive! 
It's amazing how much is going on here aroma-wise. Ginger, honey, and vanilla are incredibly prominent, with coffee adding nice subtleties as well. Bourbon is a bit mild, but it certainly doesn't detract from the rest of the beer. The flavor opens up with notes of vanilla and mocha, with latter gently rolling all the way to the end. Ginger shows up in the middle, and there's a gentle bourbon oak sensation on the aftertaste. A lot is going on here, but there's a sense of coherent balance which makes it very enjoyable. Unfortunately, the thin body lets it down a bit - more bulk could have improved the flavors going to the palate even more, not to mention send it straight to the God tier of barrel-aged stouts. Still a fantastic brew that should be sought after.
4.25/5: Gingerbread, coffee, bourbon, and it's NOT a car crash either! 864 charactersThisWangsChung, Mar 25, 2016
