4.6/5  rDev +0.9%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Pours deep black with chocolate milk head on tap @ Hardywood on release day. Big coffee aroma with underlying bourbon, chocolate, ginger, cinnamon and honey. The flavor is also big coffee with slight sweetness (less than other variants due to the amount of coffee) with slight hints of the bourbon, ginger, cinnamon, honey etc. The coffee used is absolutely wonderful, but kind of overpowers the other flavors.  It was 40 degrees outside while drinking it @ Hardywood in line on the day of the release, so it could not really warm to "drinking temperature." The  AB & BB versions were my favorite of the variants. KY Christmas morning was excellent also, but was not nearly as balanced in flavor as the others. It was a definite coffee bomb, which don't get me wrong, they used excellent coffee and was a great experience. They ran out of KYCM bottles about 20 people in front of me(raised the allotment 3 days before the release.. people were angry to say the least that they didn't change it back after seeing the longest line they have probably ever seen at HW 2 hrs before the release time), so I only had it on tap and not in the bottle at proper temperature, so I could be off of a proper review. Awesome beer Hardywood, just please come up with a better system on release day, and do not raise the allotment and then send remaining bottles to a few select stores after your best customers/fans wait in line for 4 hours to be told they will get nothing, when you could have changed it back to 3-4 bottles from 6 when you saw the insane line before opening.  Apple Brandy was brewery only, and I do not understand why this was not also.  My rating may have been higher if I would have had the chance to try a bottle at proper temperature. If you get a chance to try it, definitely go for it, but good luck finding a bottle at this point unless you want to overpay/overtrade. 1,879 charactersStolenface1, Jan 08, 2016
