4.57/5  rDev +0.2%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Deep brown to black with very little head and minimal lacing.
Aromas of coffee, vanilla, sweet malt, booze, oak, and minor ginger.
Taste is coffee, ginger, vanilla, booze, malt, and a mixture of spices - cinnamon and nutmeg
Mouthful is medium and soft with moderate carbonation and a creamy warming finish.
Hardywood did an exceptional job here balancing the flavors - nothing overpowers and all are very noticeable.  The profile changes very little from cool to warm, holding the balance throughout.  This was extremely enjoyable with a minor drawback of being almost too filling (read share the bottle).  If you have the opportunity, try this beer. 654 charactersSlack, Dec 26, 2015
