4.71/5  rDev +3.3%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.5Poured from a bomber to a spieglau stout glass.
Color is near black, light permeates the edges easily.  Thick, medium carbonation head forms but recedes in a couple minutes.  Zero lacing.
Nose is nice - ginger, coffee, and barrel are there but all very subtle.  There's a very "clean" aspect to the nose - it doesn't give as much of an indication of taste as I'd expect but very nice.
Taste - nailed it.  Just damn perfect - Hardywood could in general stand to leave their beer in barrels for a bit longer but this works perfectly for this brew.  Ginger isn't overpowered, some of the edges are smoothed (I'm not as in love with GBS as most) and this beer tastes absolutely world class.  
Feel is only taken down a slight bit because I think it could be just a touch thicker/stickier/more viscous to leave a bit more residual flavor on the finish.  It is incredibly clean for as much as it has going on - I just think a touch more body would do it well.
This is a great brew, not quite Trickery level good imho, but hopefully this will see greater production in the future. 1,078 charactersoldn00b, Dec 25, 2015
